    "British Vacillation On Approval of the Palestine Partition Plan Has Caused Economic Setback Jewish Leaders Say The following is the fourth of a series of uncensored dispatches giving a firsthand account of the sanguinary JewishArab utrugzle in Palestine which is growing in intensity as the Cnristmas season approaches By WEBB MILLER World Copyright 1937 by United Press JERUSALEM VIA LONDON Dec 23If a Jewish state is established in Palestine under the British par tition scheme it generally has been conceded that Dr Chaim Weizmann Zionisms foremost personality would be the first head of the state Prospects of the first independent Jewish state in the world since the year 65 B C when Pompey stormed Jerusalem has stirred the Imagina tion of Jews to intense discussion and speculation on the form of government Dr Weizmann is widely recognized tor his great services to the Allied cause in the World War by his dis covery of a method of extracting acetone from horse chestnuts The chiscovery undoubtedly had great in fluence in prompting Britain to promise the establishment of a Jew ish national home RESEMBLES LENIN When Dr Weizmann invented the process Britain was suffering from a critical shortage of acetone a"
